I"
<p>In this example, we are only asked to determine the <strong>left-hand limit</strong> of the function. So, substitute values to $x$ approaching $-3$ from the left.</p>

<figure style="text-align: center;">
  <img src="/images/content/DC/DC-2.5.5.png" alt="my alt text" width="400px" />
  <figcaption><em>
</em></figcaption>
</figure>

<p>Since the function is getting larger and larger as $x$ approaches $-3$ from the left,</p>

\[\begin{align*}
	\lim_{x\to -3^-} \br{ 5-\frac{1}{x+3} } &amp;= \infty	\tagans
\end{align*}\]

